FBIS4-64994 "drweu091_j_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-091 Daily Report 10 May 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Scalfaro Letter to Berlusconi on Policy Detailed Scalfaro Letter to Berlusconi on Policy Detailed LD1005170594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1430 GMT 10 May 94 LD1005170594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Text] The president's office has released details of a letter sent to Silvio Berlusconi yesterday, in which President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro draws the prime minister's attention to certain problems "where a lack of a solution" could "cause problems for the Italian Republic both inside and outside its borders." Scalfaro writes that it is about giving assurances: 1. that there will be complete faithfulness to the alliances of our foreign policy; 2. that the person in charge of the Interior Ministry will not take up stances which are contrary to the principles of national unity; and 3. that the principles of social solidarity will be respected.
